{"kind":"ruler","display":"Cleopatra I Syra","greek_form":null,"alternative_reading":null,"prenomen":null,"start_bce":-193,"end_bce":-176,"approximate":false,"uncertainty_plus_years":null,"dynasty":null,"page":null,"note":"Consort of Ptolemy V (193-180 BCE), then regent for Ptolemy VI (180-176 BCE). First Ptolemaic queen to rule without her husband. Held titles 'female Pharaoh' and 'female Horus'; appeared on coinage before her son. Full Horus name attested; prenomen not attested"}
{"kind":"ruler","display":"Cleopatra V Tryphaena","greek_form":null,"alternative_reading":"Cleopatra VI","prenomen":null,"start_bce":-79,"end_bce":-69,"approximate":false,"uncertainty_plus_years":null,"dynasty":null,"page":null,"note":"Pharaoh with Ptolemy XII (79-69 BCE). Held titles 'Daughter of Re', 'Female Ruler', 'Mistress of Two Lands' at Edfu and Philae. May be identical with 'Cleopatra VI Tryphaena' who co-ruled with Berenice IV 58-57 BCE; identity deeply contested. Prenomen not attested"}
{"kind":"ruler","display":"Cleopatra II","greek_form":null,"alternative_reading":null,"prenomen":null,"start_bce":-170,"end_bce":-116,"approximate":false,"uncertainty_plus_years":null,"dynasty":null,"page":null,"note":"Co-regent with Ptolemy VI (170-145), Ptolemy VIII (145-131, 127-116). Sole ruler 131-127 BCE. First Ptolemaic queen to rule in her own right; prenomen not attested"}
